div.p:
The encoding follows TEI P5 and is designed to support:


diplomatic transcription with abbreviation expansion;

named entity annotation with centralised authority files;

cipher text documentation with decipherment apparatus;

manuscript damage and uncertain readings;

correspondence metadata compliant with
            correspSearch.

The corpus is accompanied by two authority files:
persNames.xml: a listPerson containing all referenced persons with biographical data and VIAF identifiers;
placeNames.xml: a listPlace containing all referenced places with historical and modern names, geographic coordinates, and TGN identifiers.

The sourceDesc contains a msDesc with:
msIdentifier: settlement, repository, collection, and shelf mark (idno);
msContents / msItem: locus (folio range), title, author, language (textLang), and a summary (note type=summary);
physDesc: object description (form=letter), layout, physical condition where relevant (supportDesc / condition), and hand description (handDesc / handNote).

The encodingDesc contains:
editorialDecl: a prose description of editorial choices specific to the letter (e.g. annotation scope, cipher handling);
projectDesc: a reference to the centralised authority files.

The correspDesc records the correspondence metadata:
correspAction type=sent: sender (persName with ref), place of sending (placeName with ref), and date (date with when in ISO 8601);
correspAction type=received: recipient (persName with ref), and optionally place of reception.

list.item:
persName: primary name form. Additional
            persName elements with type=alias
            record alternative names, titles, or pseudonyms;

occupation with type classifying the role
            (values: nobility, ecclesiastic,
            diplomat, physician, military);

placeName with type=historical
            and xml:lang=it: the historical Italian
            toponym as used in the letters;
